cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a manifold-based affinity learning algorithm. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of pairwise constraints and scalability, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions low on-line time complexity, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of a generic postprocessing procedure suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in terms of security, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
